245
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Nor did the creature keep him waiting.

246
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,000
He grabbed and mauled a man on his bench.

247
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,000
Eaten up hand and foot.

248
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
Venturing closer.

249
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,000
His talon was raised to attack Beowulf.

250
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Where he lay on the bed, he was bearing in with open claw

251
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:06,000
when the alert hero's comeback and armlock forestalled him utterly.

252
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:09,000
Hateful to each was the breath of the other.

253
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Rip in the giant flesh-frame showed then.

254
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:16,000
Then an extraordinary wail arose

255
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,000
and bewildering fear came over the Danes.

256
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:23,000
A God-cursed scream and strain of catastrophe.

257
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,000
The howl of the loser.

258
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:29,000
Shoulder muscles sprang apart. A snapping of tendons. Bone locks burst.

259
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:32,000
A breach in the giant flesh-frame showed then.

260
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:36,000
To Beowulf the glory of this fight was granted.

261
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:40,000
Grendel's lot to flee the slopes fenward with flagging heart

262
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:43,000
to a den where he knew there could be no relief,

263
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,000
no refuge for a life at its very last stage

264
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,000
whose surrender day had dawned.

265
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Beowulf had cleansed Herod!

266
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:54,000
